cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.AR, cs.MM 

The paper discusses energy-efficient communication in wireless systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking (cs.NI), system optimization (cs.SY), signal processing (cs.AR), and hardware design (cs.MM). The focus on cross-layer optimization and physical layer modifications also suggests a strong connection to cs.SY and cs.AR.
